We intentionally do not keep a second always-current spec document. The living design is the combination of mycelium.sh, README.md, SKILL.md, the test suite, and the repo's own mycelium notes so the project dogfoods the tool.\n\nFresh-agent onboarding:\n1. Read README.md for the public contract.\n2. Read SKILL.md for agent workflow and conventions.\n3. Run 'mycelium.sh find decision', 'mycelium.sh find constraint', and 'mycelium.sh find warning' to load the durable reasoning layer.\n4. Run 'mycelium.sh context <file>' before touching any file.\n5. Treat archived historical design notes as lineage, not as the current contract.\n\nThe current contract should live in the visible layer (code, README, SKILL, tests) plus the invisible mycelium layer (live notes), not in a parallel markdown spec.
